---
title: Tangy Ginger Beef & Green Bean Bowls with Rice, Crispy Wonton Strips & Spicy Mayo
description: In this Asian-style bowl, ground pork and green beans are stir-fried and coated in a tangy ginger-ponzu-chili sauce. Everything comes together over a bed of fluffy rice with a shower of crunchy wonton strips and a creamy drizzle of spicy mayo.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/686d3c065ba155634794fdc2-26349a6a.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/686e5b128d751c3919190edb-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/tangy-ginger-beef-and-green-bean-bowls-686e5b128d751c3919190edb
author: HelloFresh
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 960 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 100 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1340 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
---

In a small #pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1 ¼ cups water (2 ¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary; halve crosswise.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters}, @umami ginger sauce{4%tablespoon}, half the @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 2 TBSP water, and @sugar{1/4%tsp} (all the vinegar, 4 TBSP water, and ½ tsp sugar for 4 servings). Stir in @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}. Break up meat into pieces, then stir in green beans. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until pork is cooked through and green beans are browned and tender, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir ponzu mixture into pan with pork and green beans. Cook, stirring often, until slightly thickened, ~{1%minute} more. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%TBSP} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Divide rice between #bowls{}. Top with pork and green bean stir-fry; garnish with @wonton strips{1}. Drizzle with @spicy mayo{4%tablespoon} and any remaining Sriracha to taste. Serve.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.